body:
A strange effects happens: a not removable xAxis is added to BarChart.
This is the configuration for the axis (data are provided via another method that doesn't interact with axis) and you can see in the attached image that there is a xAxis line in black with no gap to the bars that can't be hidden and a light gray xAxis with gap from the bars that is the one i can configure accessing xAxis.

I want to remove the black one.

```
chartView = [[BarChartView alloc] initWithFrame:CGRectMake(8, 0, tableView.frame.size.width-16, 130)];            
chartView.delegate = self;
            chartView.userInteractionEnabled = NO;
            chartView.backgroundColor = [UIColor colorWithHexString:@"#88FFFFFF"];
            chartView.descriptionText = @"";
            chartView.noDataTextDescription = @"You need to provide data for the chart.";

            chartView.drawGridBackgroundEnabled = NO;
            chartView.drawBarShadowEnabled = NO;
            chartView.gridBackgroundColor = [UIColor clearColor];


            ChartYAxis *rightAxis = chartView.rightAxis;
            rightAxis.drawGridLinesEnabled = NO;
            rightAxis.drawAxisLineEnabled = NO;
            rightAxis.drawLabelsEnabled = NO;

            ChartYAxis *leftAxis = chartView.leftAxis;
            leftAxis.drawGridLinesEnabled = NO;
            leftAxis.drawAxisLineEnabled = NO;
            leftAxis.drawLabelsEnabled = NO;


            ChartXAxis *xAxis = chartView.xAxis;
            xAxis.labelPosition = XAxisLabelPositionBottom;
            xAxis.drawGridLinesEnabled = NO;
            xAxis.drawAxisLineEnabled = YES;
            xAxis.axisLineWidth = 1.0;
            xAxis.axisLineColor = [UIColor lightGrayColor];
            xAxis.labelTextColor = [UIColor lightGrayColor];
            xAxis.labelFont = [UIFont systemFontOfSize:10 weight:UIFontWeightLight];

```

